    <!-- OUT-OF-SAMPLE VALIDATION -->
    <div class="section">
      <h2>Out-of-Sample Validation</h2>
      <p class="prose">The strongest evidence for any model is its performance on data it was never fitted to. The Power Law was first identified by Giovanni Santostasi in 2014 and formally published by Matthew Me&#x17E;inskis in 2018. Every year since publication has been an out-of-sample test &mdash; the model was fitted to data that existed at the time, and subsequent prices have continued tracking the trajectory.</p>
      <p class="prose">The chart below demonstrates this directly: the green line shows the Power Law regression fitted to only the first five years of data (2010&ndash;2014). The orange dots show all actual prices since then. If the early-data model were merely overfitting, its projection would diverge from reality as time passed. Instead, the early-fitted regression has tracked Bitcoin's actual price across the subsequent decade with remarkable fidelity &mdash; through multiple bull and bear cycles, regulatory shifts, and black-swan events.</p>
